<HL>
   Mediq Unit Completes Merger
</HL>
<DATE>
07/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MED
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   PENNSAUKEN, N.J. -- NutraMax Products Inc. and Aid-Pack
Inc., a unit of Mediq Inc., said they have completed a
previously announced merger, valued at about $18 million.
   Mediq said it owns 81.7% of the merged companies, which
will operate and trade shares over-the-counter as NutraMax
Products Inc. Mediq said it received about 120 million shares
of NutraMax as a result of the merger. NutraMax shares have
been trading in the over-the-counter market.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Aid-Pack, a Gloucester, Mass.-based maker and distributor
of feminine personal-care products, had sales of about $13.1
million last year.
   NutraMax, formerly based in Ft. Lee, N.J., and now in
Gloucester, distributes and markets health and beauty
products in the U.S. and Japan. The company had sales of
about $347,000 last year.
   Mediq, based in Pennsauken, N.J., sells health-care
products and services. The company had sales of about $350
million last year.
