<HL>
   Money-Fund Assets
   Rose $1.93 Billion
   In the Latest Week
</HL>
<DATE>
07/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C19
</SO>
<IN>
MUTUAL AND MONEY-MARKET FUNDS (FND)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Assets of the nation's 513 money-market
funds rose $1.93 billion to $391.84 billion, in the week
ended Wednesday, according to the Investment Company
Institute.
   Assets of 251 general-purpose funds rose $1.21 billion to
$135.91 billion; 102 brokerdealer funds rose $356.6 million
to $160.75 billion; and 160 institutional funds rose $366
million to $95.18 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Dr. Jacob Dreyer, vice president and chief economist at
the Washington trade association, said that money funds
posted the third consecutive large increase in assets,
despite lagging yields resulting from declines in yields on
direct money-market instruments.
</TEXT>
