<HL>
   International Brief -- Asahi Glass Co.:
   Pretax Profit Gained 2.3%
   To a Record in First Half
</HL>
<DATE>
07/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   J.AHG
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Asahi Glass Co. said pretax profit in the first half rose
2.3% to a record 40.14 billion yen ($267.6 million).
   The Japanese chemical and glass maker had profit of 39.23
billion yen in the year-earlier period.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Sales rose 12% to a record 487.68 billion yen from 437.04
billion yen. Net income also grew to a record, at 21.84
billion yen, or 18.74 yen a share, up 3.9% from 21.02 billion
yen, or 18.08 yen a share. The company plans to pay an
unchanged dividend of 4.5 yen a share.
   Sales of glass and construction materials, accounting for
51.6% of total sales, gained 13% to 251.81 billion yen. Sales
of fabricated glass had strong gains, reflecting domestic
automobile sales, which more than compensated for a decline
in auto exports, officials said.
   Sales of chemicals, accounting for 36.2% of overall sales,
gained 6.8% to 176.4 billion yen.
   Earnings were damped by higher labor and transportation
costs, a spokesman said. Higher raw materials costs, largely
reflecting the yen's weakness in the first quarter, also hurt
profit, he said.
</TEXT>
