   Business Brief -- Eldon Industries Inc.:
   Office-Products Company
   Looks at Business Options
</HL>
<DATE>
07/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   ELD
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Eldon Industries Inc., an office-products maker, said it
is evaluating a number of strategic alternatives, including a
sale or business combination.
   The Inglewood, Calif., company said it has had preliminary
discussions with several companies, but that it has reached
no definitive agreements and can give no assurance any sale
or transaction will occur. Eldon said it has hired a
financial adviser to assist in the evaluation. It did not
identify the adviser.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Eldon posted net income of $2.1 million, or 23 cents a
share, for the first quarter ended March 24 compared with
year-earlier profit of $1.9 million, or 21 cents a share.
Sales were $26.3 million compared with $25.1 million a year
earlier.
   For the 53-week period ended Dec. 30, Eldon had net income
of $8.6 million, or 91 cents a share, compared with year-ago
profit of $7.6 million, or 81 cents a share. Sales were
$112.6 million compared with $101.4 million a year earlier.
   Eldon closed yesterday at $17.875, up 62.5 cents, in New
York Stock Exchange composite trading.
