<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Anchor Savings Bank reported fourth-quarter net income of
$40.9 million, compared with a year-earlier net loss,
reflecting gains from asset sales plus improved operations.
   The earnings for the quarter equal $2.15 a share, compared
with a loss of $26.9 million, or $1.75 a share, in the
year-earlier period.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Hewlett, N.Y., savings bank said that excluding $45.7
million of pretax gains on asset sales and a $3.8 million
addition to its provision for credit losses, it reported
profit for the quarter of $1.9 million. The comparable figure
for the year-earlier period was a $3 million net loss.
   The asset sales are part of Anchor's plan to bring it into
full compliance with federal capital requirements.
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Anchor
shares closed at $1.6875, up 31.25 cents.
